  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Supervisor (Day/Night)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Site Operations</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Supervise and coordinate the works of site personnel including that of subcontractor and suppliers.</li>\n  <li>Monitor daily activities and provide the necessary reports to the Site / Project Manager.</li>\n  <li>Support the inspection works with the Client’s representative.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Safety Compliances</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ensure adherence by stakeholders on their Method of Statements/Procedures (MOPs, MOSs), Health Risk Assessments (HRAs) and Safe Work Procedures (SWPs).</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) standards and requirements on site by personnel, subcontractors and vendors.</li>\n  <li>Identify Safety non-compliances or incompatibility of works, and report them to Safety Department.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Quality Controls</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare the necessary documentation for inspection with client.</li>\n  <li>Ensure accuracy in documentation furbished by subcontractors, vendors, and suppliers.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that non-compliances raised are reported and rectified immediately.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Resource Management</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate materials delivery on site and ensure proper handling and storage of materials.</li>\n  <li>Ensure and maintain accurate records and documentation of submissions, delivered goods (i.e. delivery orders, drawings), site inventories and material usage.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Documentation and Reporting</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Provide daily and weekly reports to site manager.</li>\n  <li>Maintain daily records on site including but not limited to inspection forms, daily site records, manpower deployments and safety matters.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Experience in Project Supervision, preferably in data centre or critical environment.</li>\n  <li>Certification in workplace safety (eg. WSQ, WSH) preferred.</li>\n  <li>Positive proactive attitude and ethical behaviour.</li>\n  <li>Team player with ability to work independently and resolve challenges in a fast-paced environment.</li>\n  <li>Excellent interpersonal, communication and collaborative skills.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Microsoft Word, Excel and PowerPoint).</li>\n</ul>",
